			<div class="content" id="post-content-3765245">
									

<p>No actual zoo, but they probably work in tandem with local animal shelters and can have tours where they show people animals they are rehabilitating (if they’re public-friendly). Anomalies are generally known, but mostly just that things around here are “a bit odd”.</p>
<p>For clarification, I would think that someone living in the town would sorta know about these things, but upon becoming part of Wilson’s Wildlife Solutions they would still be surprised at just <em>how</em> weird everything can get.</p>
<p>Note that they don’t have many facilities. Having a dedicated zoo would probably be out of their budget (or just too expensive and dangerous to be worth it even if they could do it).</p>

